Abstract = {The paper aims at illustrating the long-standing relationship between
   computational science and legal logic. In a highly discretionary area of
   human activity, such as criminal justice, artificial intelligence may
   appear a potential, effective solution to many recurrent conundrums.
   Moving from the current achievements of artificial intelligence, the
   paper offers a reflection on the possible role of these technologies, to
   understand how they can contribute to restore some effectiveness to a
   system that has lost, in the eyes of citizens, credibility and
   trustworthiness.},
