   NETWORK, DEC 10-13, 2020},
Organization = {IEEE; IEEE Comp Soc; IBM; Ankura},
Abstract = {We study a recent dataset documenting the nature of gang involvement
   among 14-25 year-olds participating in the Los Angeles Mayor's Office of
   Gang Reduction and Youth Development (GRYD) Intervention Family Case
   Management Program. We use natural language processing techniques,
   including emotion classification and textual clustering, to perform
   quantitative analyses of free-form responses in the data. These analyses
   yield insights into the effectiveness of the program and provide a
   better understanding of its participants. We also compare several
   computational techniques and remark on their relative effectiveness in
   application to this dataset.},
