   Tech Comm Intelligent Informat; Journal Healthcare Informat Res; Hlth
   Data Sci},
Abstract = {In this three-hour tutorial, participants will learn how to use the ISLE
   e-learning platform to deliver health informatics and analytics
   instruction. ISLE is an open-source e-learning platform that allows
   students and professionals to explore data and concepts interactively
   without coding. The platform has been used for multiple years for both
   statistics instruction and a variety of other subjects including the
   humanities and criminology. In a live demonstration with voluntary
   audience participation, we will showcase an interactive e-learning
   lesson developed as an in-class activity for a Health Information
   Systems class at Carnegie Mellon University on some of the methods that
   are commonly used in the fields of data science and statistics,
   including logistic regression, clustering methods, random forests, and
   optimization as they pertain to healthcare analytics.},
