   INDIA, DEC 14-16, 2017},
Abstract = {A number of machine learning algorithms are avail-able for detection of
   different types of network anomalies. How-ever, network anomalies vary
   in their requirement for detection and there is no general method or
   algorithm that is applicable to all types of anomalies which may occur
   in a network. The paper divulges the application of different available
   methods in comparison mode and analyses the rationale of the algorithms.
   Freely available databases are used for study and used as a benchmark
   for testing different methods of network anomalies. The benchmarks are
   used for testing accuracy. Such accuracy threshold indicates the
   required data validation. Validated data may be used forensic purpose.
   The data for Digital forensic must pass a threshold value from the test
   data. Determination of efficiency of methods is additional analytical
   aspect of the paper that is achieved in Python coding and in well
   formulated steps.The paper gives an overview of the process for finding
   network anomalies and data accuracy for digital forensic use.},
